## Summary

Add a VitePress docs site under `docs/` (landing page + getting-started from README) and a GitHub Pages deploy workflow on push to `main`.

## Context

Tasken currently ships a `README.md` plus a `docs/` tree of design notes (journeys, operations, stories, SLSA), but no rendered documentation site. This PR adds a minimal VitePress setup that consumes the existing markdown (so nothing is duplicated) and wires up GitHub Pages deploy via the official `actions/*` trio, all action references pinned to commit SHAs.

## Changes

- **`docs/.vitepress/config.mts`** — VitePress config with `srcDir: '.'` rooted at `docs/`, hero/feature blocks, nav + sidebar linking to `/` and `/getting-started`.
- **`docs/index.md`** — Converted to the VitePress home layout (hero + features) while preserving the existing docs subdirectory listing.
- **`docs/getting-started.md`** — New page sourced from the README's *Implementations / Quick Start / Features / Quality Gates / License* sections.
- **`package.json`** — VitePress dev dependency + `docs:dev` / `docs:build` / `docs:preview` scripts.
- **`.gitignore`** — Exclude `node_modules/`, `docs/.vitepress/dist/`, `docs/.vitepress/cache/`, `package-lock.json`.
- **`.github/workflows/docs.yml`** — Builds on push to `main` (and `workflow_dispatch`), uploads `docs/.vitepress/dist`, deploys via the official Pages actions.

