| `actions/deploy-pages`                | v4  | `d6db90164ac5ed86f2b6aed7e0febac5b3c0c03e`   |

## First-time repo setup

GitHub Pages deploy requires the repo to have Pages enabled with **Source: GitHub Actions**. After merge:

1. Repo Settings → Pages → set Source to **GitHub Actions** (one-time).
2. The workflow creates the `github-pages` environment automatically; first deploy will provision it.

## Testing

Local preview:

```bash
npm install
npm run docs:dev    # http://localhost:5173
npm run docs:build  # outputs docs/.vitepress/dist
```

CI verification: after merge to `main`, the `Docs` workflow runs; the `deploy` job publishes to the `github-pages` environment. The site URL is exposed as the environment URL and via `${{ steps.deployment.outputs.page_url }}`.

